translate ru HassarPath4_f57ea641:
    # "In the days that followed, Sarah found her life adapting an odd rhythm."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_b183e5c1:
    # "Unable to leave the sanctum, and finding no hint of an exit that would allow her to escape, she simply took to exploring it."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_a552452a:
    # "Everything she might have desired was available to her."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_a52241af:
    # "Her room was kept in pristine condition. If there were servants, Sarah suspected they must have learned to move quietly, for she never saw any."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_26c753cf:
    # "She cycled from her room, to the bathhouse, the gardens, the library."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_78c5eebe:
    # "Each time she passed through the halls, safe and provided for, she could not help but feel guilty about her situation."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_5bdfc67e:
    # "She was no fool, and she knew that in the city of Al'Gahaem, her people were being broken by her conquerors."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_4cdd390d:
    # "And here she was, a valued guest of the very man who had caused that very calamity."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_a8d9541f:
    # "Sitting on the edge of her bed, Sarah tried to recall how long she'd been here."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_bc91d2a5:
    # "It hadn't even been that long, and still she found her days seemingly bleeding into one another."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d3841526:
    # "A life of only luxury and no obligation, seemed to not just relax her body but also her mind. She felt less sharp with each passing day."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d5550582:
    # "As she tried to recall the days, Sarah realized as well that it been a good number of days since she had last seen anything of the Khan as well."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_9df76422:
    # "She passed Naydeen, Sophia and Ayaka in the halls."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_a58f3e45:
    # "Each was nice enough, and at times she even spoke and spend the day with them, but it all seemed oddly weightless."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_53fd31c7:
    # "Her jailor did not come to punish her, but she almost wished he would. To give her someone to rage against amidst the meaningless passing days."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_e9e52340:
    # "Having spoken with Naydeen, Sarah learned that this was not uncommon."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_3cdaf4b0:
    # "The Khan came and went as he pleased, and theirs was not to question the how and why of him."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_9650472a:
    # "Absent any real challenge, Sarah had found her way towards the library."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_0e56ae18:
    # "At least reading a good book might keep her mind occupied and sharp."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_1c9644d1:
    # "Wandering the many bookcases, Sarah took in the collection."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_716c44ab:
    # "The library was vast and well stocked."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_bb4aec78:
    # "Most of the sanctum suffered under the desert heat, but here, the air was cool and soft on the skin."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_7c24969a:
    # "They had to, Sarah realized, if only to preserve the books."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_11d856c9:
    # "As she made her way through, she carefully pulled some books from the shelves, placing the collection on the table to read later."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_e3b67b0a:
    # "The books quickly grew to a sizeable pile."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_6c7adbbb:
    # "In the sanctum, it was easy to feel alone, but at the same time she would often accidentally run into the other women."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_12237cf3:
    # "The library was an exception, with Sarah having only seen Naydeen use it on one other occasion."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_fad57890:
    # "As she pulled the last volume from the shelf, Sarah suddenly found a glimmer catch her eye."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_ebc59077:
    # "Most of the library was soft, muted tones, and with little natural light, it was strange to find anything stand out."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_4395f0f7:
    # "She placed the book among the others and returned to where she had seen the object glint."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_c8b5385b:
    # "As she carefully looked across the floor, Sarah finally managed to find what had first caught her attention."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_65776e05:
    # "Dust, made of seemingly polished metal."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_89df41c1:
    # "Sarah bend down and ran her fingers across the glitter."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_ffffd7ea:
    # "On the top of her fingers, the metal dustings seemed to almost shine."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_2282268a:
    # "Sarah looked around, wondering where if anything this might have come from."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_4249f101:
    # "Stone. Wood. Books. Rugs. This seemed to be everything here. Nothing that was made out of metal, or would have left scraps like this."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_18931e03:
    # "As she carefully studied the room, Sarah's eyes fell back on where she had first found the scraps of metal."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_69ae2f01:
    # "Studying it with more attention, she realized that all around the metal scraps were small scratches in the surface of the stone floor."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d2073495:
    # "They seemed ordinary enough, the kind of wear and tear any palace might go through, except for the fact that all the scratches ran along line."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_e3c1c80e:
    # "Not a line, Sarah realized, more like a cresent."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_eed243a1:
    # "Tracing the line from the floor to the wall where it seemingly emerged, Sarah realized that the scratches were familar to her."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_72288624:
    # "They were the kind you would expect on the ground where a door had swung open again and again, slowly leaving scratches in the floor."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d7e61c0a:
    # "But there was only the solid wall of stone in front of her."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_ea60aa02:
    # "Having grown up in Castle Reinmeer, Sarah was no stranger to the concept of secret tunnels."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_c580e63e:
    # "Every castle seemed to have them, most often build to safeguard the royal family, but just as often build and forgotten."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_f5a371fc:
    # "Sarah's heart began to race. Something new and exciting, but perhaps more even than that, it might even offer an escape."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_7b05e35e:
    # "Her hands began to explore the solid stone wall, carefully scratching and pulling at every inch of it."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_5cda944d:
    # "Slowly, her fingers traced every line, pressed upon every brick."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_ba1d05e4:
    # "Just when she imagined it was pointless, her finger found a small gap in the wall."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_477bb114:
    # "Sliding it in, she heard a soft clicking sound, deep from within the stone wall."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_58ebad3d:
    # "The door unlocked and softly swung open."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_34b93f6d:
    # "The size and solidness of it was belied by how soundlessly it seemed to move. It almost floated across the floor."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_23cda6b8:
    # "For a moment, Sarah only dared to stare into the secret tunnel."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_314ae327:
    # "Her heart was pounding in her chest."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_60955ea0:
    # "Secret...who was to say it was even secret? What if the Khan knew of this tunnel?"
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_c5071970:
    # "What if he discovered that she had found it? What if he would punish her for it?"
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_0085f22b:
    # "Her mind was racing with possibility, and yet, she could not suppress the urge to enter the tunnel, no matter the risk."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_3ff1507d:
    # "As she stepped in, she instantly felt the air change."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_4fd0405b:
    # "The air in the library was soft, but here it was cold. She hadn't felt air this cold since she'd been taken to the desert."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d75f79f9:
    # "Taking a few steps further inside, Sarah began to feel a draft run past her body."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_544ebec6:
    # "Her mind raced, considering where it might be coming from."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_305f525a:
    # "Outside. What if it came from outside of the sanctum?"
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_0c7200a7:
    # "Her heart swelled with the possibility. Freedom. She could be free."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_6f9aa38d:
    # "No sooner did her heart swell than did it shatter."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_af8ed1b4:
    # "A loud sound called out to her."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_0eb2e02f:
    # h "Sarah? Where are you?"
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_fedbdffb:
    # "She turned towards the voice of the Khan."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_7bcc47da:
    # "The libary. He was in there."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d532bbe0:
    # "Did she run? What if this would prove her only chance..."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_4b07c833:
    # "She shook her head, forcing herself to think clearly."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_03cd6a28:
    # "Sarah didn't know where the tunnel would lead to, if it went anywhere at all."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_9b05268b:
    # "If she tried to run now, the odds were just as good that she would get lost, or end up nowhere at all."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_777fa496:
    # "Rushing back through the secret door, Sarah stepped back into the library."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_f10c84f7:
    # "With a soft touch from her hand, she forced the secret door to close again."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_e1c4d81c:
    # "She feared a sound, but to her relief, the door closed as silently as it had opened."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_200938b2:
    # "Sarah closed her eyes and steeled herself to be calm."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_7b0a5aa0:
    # "Suppress any emotion. Don't show him anything."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d7acbeb0:
    # "Sarah walked out from behind the bookcases."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_070add07:
    # s "Aah, Khan Hassar, I thought I heard you."
    s ""

translate ru HassarPath4_9f6934d2:
    # "She saw his eyes roaming her body, but resting on her face. Those piercing eyes."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_519bb77d:
    # "Was he looking for some hint in her face that revealed her secret, or did she only imagine it because her mind was guilty?"
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_eba32a00:
    # h "I went to look for you, but none of the others had seen you."
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_40aa162e:
    # "Sarah nodded."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_ecd4ccf3:
    # s "I wanted to be alone today, I thought I would retire to the library."
    s ""

translate ru HassarPath4_3a9aa824:
    # s "I hope that I haven't made you upset?"
    s ""

translate ru HassarPath4_b04807bd:
    # "Sarah looked him in the eyes. Was she acting too submissively? Or not enough? She tempered herself."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_367d2256:
    # "She only saw his smiling face."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_6a7967b9:
    # h "Of course not. You must feel free to explore the sanctum. It was build for you and the others."
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_40aa162e_1:
    # "Sarah nodded."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_039430ca:
    # s "Thank you, Khan Hassar."
    s ""

translate ru HassarPath4_bfd6c9d3:
    # "A moment of silence lingered between them."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_6bb778ae:
    # "His eyes drifted towards the large stack of books on the table."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_8b170956:
    # h "I see you have been making good use of the library."
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_536579ef:
    # h "I'm glad, I don't think it's seen much use since it was first build."
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_11105c69:
    # "His eyes fell back on her."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_9329dada:
    # "Sarah could see his eyes roaming freely across her body."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_7948a8d7:
    # "Once, not even that long ago, she could not have imagined tolerating this from anyone."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d96d342c:
    # "Now she was in no place to stop him."
    ""

translate ru HassarPath4_d594f6b2:
    # h "Tell me, what book were you searching for back there?"
    h ""

translate ru HassarPath4_91d1d27e:
    # "The Khan gestured towards where Sarah had come from. Where the secret door was."
    ""

